                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17860719-18-off84 t17860719-18-victim257"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17860719-18-person258">
                  ROBERT
                   PAYNE
               <interp inst="t17860719-18-person258" type="surname" value="PAYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-person258" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-person258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I live with Mr. Brown, a pawn-broker in the Strand; I have a great coat, which I took in on the 10th of July, of the prisoner; he said it was his own property; I did not know him before he pledged it<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178607190036"></xptr> for 4 s. it was in the course of the afternoon; this is the great coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17860719-18-person259">
                  JOHN
                   AUSTIN
               <interp inst="t17860719-18-person259" type="surname" value="AUSTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-person259" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-person259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a carpenter, at No. 1, Burleigh-Court, in the Strand; the prisoner came and lodged with me two or three nights, in the same room, and I lost a coat and a pair of shoes; I traced this coat, and found where it was pledged; I know it by a hole burned in one of the skirts very soon after I had it, and one of the cuffs is torn off; I saw it on Saturday the 8th of July; I missed it on Tuesday following; the prisoner had left my lodgings.</p>
               <p>PRISONER'S DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I have not a friend in the world that will appear to my character, therefore I have only to leave it to the mercy of the Court.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17860719-18-verdict86" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-verdict86" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17860719-18-punish87" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17860719-18-punish87" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
